{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Plan re-review after box-adaptation: VERDICT=PASS (0 blocking, 0 indeterminate, 20 advisory). Triage:\n\nREMEDIATED IN PLAN: What-section + AC1 updated to 'review-bot ONLY; replication/g2p/refs-meta DETECT-ONLY in v1' (removed the stale auto-apply wording); Stability §3 health-check reworded to liveness (process up + /health 200) consistent with box-adaptation §3; ADR 0026 added (docs/adr/0026-autodeploy-on-box-timer.md) covering on-box-timer-vs-GH-OIDC, copy-based build context, v1 review-bot-only narrowing, back-out.\n\nRESOLVED BY COMMIT (reviewer compared the plan to the STALE committed autodeploy.sh — old git-checkout version; the box-adapted code was uncommitted in the working tree): 'no rsync / still uses /opt/rebar/src / no MIRROR_DIR / auto-applies replication+g2p / install-autodeploy.sh missing / first-run doesn't seed from .deployed_ref' — ALL implemented in the working-tree rewrite (mirror clone + rsync --delete + HTTPS guard + detect-only config + corrected systemd paths + .deployed_ref seed) and install-autodeploy.sh created; they align once committed.\n\nJUDGED INVALID / justified-kept:\n- bash '**' claimed to need bash 5.0+: FALSE. Arithmetic '**' works since bash 3.x; the box runs bash 5.2.15 (verified via SSM: 60*(2**3)=480). No change.\n- python3 fork in log/err (perf): kept deliberately — correct JSON escaping > a sed hack that can mis-escape; ~1440 short-lived forks/day on a 2-min timer is negligible.\n- first-build-no-:prev health-fail edge: on the box review-bot:latest always exists (bot is running) so have_prev=1 in practice; documented, not a live risk.\n\nVALIDATION EVIDENCE: live SSM --dry-run of the exact rsync exclude set on the box confirmed .env is preserved (0 delete matches) and only stray *.bak files would be removed; mirror clone bootstrapped, remote is https, main tip resolved."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783107200815153001,"uuid":"c73e566b-568e-4f75-8bb5-42a8c093452e"}